canonical:
  title: 謝御酒御衣起居表
  author: 李穡
  language: lzh
  text: 身居鰈域偏承雨露之恩目注龍墀倍祝岡陵之壽
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝御酒御衣起居表
  author: 李穡
  language: lzh
  text: 身居鰈域。偏承雨露之恩。目注龍墀。倍祝岡陵之壽。
korean:
  title: 술과 의복을 내려준 데 대하여 사례하는 글
  author: 이색
  language: kor
  text: 몸이 동쪽 지경에 거하면서 편벽되게 우로(雨露)의 은혜를 받았고, 눈이 황제의 뜰을 바라보매 배나 강릉(岡陵)의 수를 축원하옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0410_010_0020&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Memento of Thanks for the Royal Wine and Robes
  author: Lee Saek
  language: eng
  text: |-
    My body dwells in these eastern lands,
    yet I receive the sovereign's rain and dew with undeserved abundance.
    My eyes turn toward the dragon throne,
    and my heart doubles its prayers for the emperor's longevity—
    may the hills of his fortune stand eternal.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Rain and dew (雨露) is a classical metaphor for the emperor's benevolence and grace dispensed upon his subjects.
  - key: ''
    value: The dragon throne refers to the imperial court, using the traditional symbol of imperial authority.
  - key: ''
    value: 岡陵 (Gangneung/the hills) alludes to the Taoist concept of celestial mountains and immortality, here expressing wishes for the ruler's eternal prosperity.
